{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I would say the docs are wrong.\r\n\r\nIt should be: `Black is nearest, white is farthest.`","created_at":"2018-02-15T14:23:59.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13329#issuecomment-365941661","id":365941661,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13329","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2NTk0MTY2MQ==","updated_at":"2018-02-15T14:24:11.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/365941661","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"`MeshDepthMaterial` was previously \"white nearest\", but was inverted in #8573. See [this comment](https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/8573#issuecomment-207771253).\r\n\r\nIn fact, in `UnpackDepthRGBAShader`, white is nearest:\r\n\r\n    \"float depth = 1.0 - unpackRGBAToDepth( texture2D( tDiffuse, vUv ) );\",\r\n\r\nAlso, if the background is black when rendering a depth map, then, to be consistent, far depths should also be black.\r\n\r\nIMO, that is a compelling reason to revert.\r\n\r\nSo I would say the docs are fine, and `MeshDepthMaterial` should be reverted to \"white nearest\" for `BasicDepthPacking`.\r\n\r\n\/ping @bhouston \r\n","created_at":"2018-02-15T19:29:43.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13329#issuecomment-366035827","id":366035827,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13329","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2NjAzNTgyNw==","updated_at":"2018-02-15T19:29:43.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/366035827","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"What is the convention used by the native depth texture extension?  I believe that it uses near as 0.0, and far as 1.0 right -- because it is using Normalized Device Coordinates right?\r\n\r\nThe RGBA packed depth should probably use the same convention for consistency.  Thus far is White, and near is Black.","created_at":"2018-02-15T19:44:57.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13329#issuecomment-366040105","id":366040105,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13329","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2NjA0MDEwNQ==","updated_at":"2018-02-15T19:44:57.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/366040105","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/588541?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/bhouston","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU4ODU0MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"bhouston","type":"User","id":588541,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"If you are drawing to a native depth texture or a simulated RGBA packed depth texture, you have to clear to 1.0 or White: https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/dev\/examples\/js\/postprocessing\/SAOPass.js#L237\r\n\r\nJust like if you are drawing to a normal buffer, you need to clear with (0.5, 0.5, 1.0), a normal vector pointing down z axis: https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/dev\/examples\/js\/postprocessing\/SAOPass.js#L244","created_at":"2018-02-15T19:48:42.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13329#issuecomment-366041033","id":366041033,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13329","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2NjA0MTAzMw==","updated_at":"2018-02-15T19:48:42.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/366041033","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/588541?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/bhouston","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU4ODU0MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"bhouston","type":"User","id":588541,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"It is true, in NDC, far is 1. But the colors for grayscale (visual) rendering can be anything we want.\r\n\r\nIn https:\/\/threejs.org\/examples\/webgl_materials_channels.html, there is no clearing to white, and the background and depth colors are inconsistent.\r\n\r\nAlso, `SAOPass` uses `UnpackDepthRGBAShader` which has white nearest.\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2018-02-15T20:12:28.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13329#issuecomment-366047343","id":366047343,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13329","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2NjA0NzM0Mw==","updated_at":"2018-02-15T20:12:28.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/366047343","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"In this end, this is just a choice we have to make.  I prefer to be as least interesting as possible thus if there is already a coordinate system assumed for this parameter elsewhere, such as in NDC, I advocate we standardize on it, rather than having difference choices in different places.\r\n\r\nBut I do not care that much about this.","created_at":"2018-02-20T03:46:05.000Z","html_url":"http